3. Differential form

Define a local intelligence increment:

dI_t = \Phi(s_t, a_t, f_t, c_t)\,dt

Where \Phi measures whether the local cycle produced real gain.

A simple expansion is:

dI_t = \alpha P_t + \beta A_t + \gamma T_t + \delta R_t - \epsilon E_t

Where:
	•	P_t = perceptual accuracy
	•	A_t = action quality
	•	T_t = transfer/generalization gained
	•	R_t = recovery/adaptation from mismatch
	•	E_t = error, illusion, rigidity, or wasted motion

So the total intelligence over an interval is:

I(T) = I(0) + \int_0^T \left(\alpha P_t + \beta A_t + \gamma T_t + \delta R_t - \epsilon E_t \right)dt

Meaning:

intelligence is the accumulated integral of successful adaptive cycles minus accumulated distortion.

