I_t = I_t^{\text{claimed}} + I_t^{\text{verified}}

Before stress, a system may appear more capable than it is.
After the break:

I_{t+1}^{\text{verified}} = \mathcal{B}(I_t)

Where the break filters out false coherence.

So:

\mathcal{B}(I_t) \le I_t^{\text{claimed}}

and equality holds only when the structure was genuine.

This gives the law:

Break Verification Law

\text{Real intelligence} = \text{that which survives stress and reorganizes coherently}

